      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, thanks. So if the body is basically recycling the pyruvate through gluconeogenesis, does that mean the \"burn\" is actually the lactic acid itself, or is it something else happening during that metabolic shift? Could you clarify what specifically triggers that immediate sensation in the muscle fibers?",
